ciscoUnityMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-unity@cisco.com
ciscoUnityMIB.description: The MIB Module for the management of Cisco Unity server. Cisco Unity is a Unified Communications solution that provides advanced, convergence-based communication services. The MIB presents provision and statistics information. ACRONYMS AMIS Analog Messaging Interface Standard MWI Message Waiting Indicator TRAP Telephone Record and Playback TTS Text-To-Speech UM Unified Messaging VMI Visual Messaging Interface VPIM Voice Profile for Internet Mail

CiscoUnityIndex.name: CiscoUnityIndex
CiscoUnityIndex.description: This textual convention is used as the Index into a table. A positive value is used to identify a unique entry in the table.

CiscoUnityServerStatus.name: CiscoUnityServerStatus
CiscoUnityServerStatus.description: This textual convention is used to indicate the current status of the local Unity server. stopped(1) The main Cisco Unity process is stopped starting(2) The main Cisco Unity process is starting running(3) The main Cisco Unity process is in normal operational mode stopping(4) The main Cisco Unity process is shutting down

ciscoUnityTable.name: ciscoUnityTable
ciscoUnityTable.description: The table containing information about all the Unity servers on the network visible to the local Unity server.

ciscoUnityEntry.name: ciscoUnityEntry
ciscoUnityEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Unity table, containing the information about a Unity server.

ciscoUnityIndex.name: ciscoUnityIndex
ciscoUnityIndex.description: An arbitrary integer, selected by the local Unity, which uniquely identifies a Unity server on the network.

ciscoUnityName.name: ciscoUnityName
ciscoUnityName.description: The host name of the Unity server.

ciscoUnityVersion.name: ciscoUnityVersion
ciscoUnityVersion.description: The version number of the Unity server software.

ciscoUnityPortTable.name: ciscoUnityPortTable
ciscoUnityPortTable.description: The table containing information about the configuration of ports on the local Unity server.

ciscoUnityPortEntry.name: ciscoUnityPortEntry
ciscoUnityPortEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Port table, containing the information about the port configuration on the local Unity server.

ciscoUnityPortIndex.name: ciscoUnityPortIndex
ciscoUnityPortIndex.description: An arbitrary integer, selected by the local Unity, which uniquely identifies a port on the local Unity server.

ciscoUnityPortNumber.name: ciscoUnityPortNumber
ciscoUnityPortNumber.description: The Unity voice messaging port number.

ciscoUnityPortIntegration.name: ciscoUnityPortIntegration
ciscoUnityPortIntegration.description: The phone system integration to which this port belongs. This could be Cisco CallManager or a traditional PBX.

ciscoUnityPortExtension.name: ciscoUnityPortExtension
ciscoUnityPortExtension.description: The extension for the port as assigned on the phone system.

ciscoUnityPortEnabled.name: ciscoUnityPortEnabled
ciscoUnityPortEnabled.description: This indicates whether this port is enabled on the local Unity server.

ciscoUnityPortAnswerCalls.name: ciscoUnityPortAnswerCalls
ciscoUnityPortAnswerCalls.description: This indicates whether this port is designated to answer incoming calls.

ciscoUnityPortMessageNotif.name: ciscoUnityPortMessageNotif
ciscoUnityPortMessageNotif.description: This indicates whether this port is designated for notifying subscribers of messages.

ciscoUnityPortDialoutMWI.name: ciscoUnityPortDialoutMWI
ciscoUnityPortDialoutMWI.description: This indicates whether this port is designated for turning MWIs on and off.

ciscoUnityPortAMISDelivery.name: ciscoUnityPortAMISDelivery
ciscoUnityPortAMISDelivery.description: This indicates whether this port is designated for making outbound AMIS calls to deliver voice messages from Unity subscribers to users on another voice messaging system.

ciscoUnityPortTRAPConnection.name: ciscoUnityPortTRAPConnection
ciscoUnityPortTRAPConnection.description: This indicates whether this port is designated for use by subscribers as a Telephone Recording And Playback (TRAP) device in Unity web applications and e-mail clients.

ciscoUnityPortActivity.name: ciscoUnityPortActivity
ciscoUnityPortActivity.description: The port activity of the voice mail port. This value is available to monitor port activity over time. The specific value of this object is not as useful as monitoring for the changing of this value. During normal operation this value should change several times during a call. You can use this value to watch for abnormal operation that might indicate a problem with this voice mail port. For example, if you monitor this value and do not detect a change in value for a long time (like 60 minutes) it could be an indication of a problem with that voice mail port. There are other explanations as well so more investigation on the server should be conducted before taking any action with the voice mail port.

ciscoUnityPortObjectId.name: ciscoUnityPortObjectId
ciscoUnityPortObjectId.reference: RFC-4122 A Universally Unique IDentifier (UUID) URN Namespace.
ciscoUnityPortObjectId.description: A globally unique, system-generated identifier for a port object. The ObjectId (UUID or GUID) uniquely identifies the port for the lifetime of this port. A UUID is 128 bits long, and can guarantee uniqueness across space and time.

ciscoUnityServerState.name: ciscoUnityServerState

ciscoUnityPortsOutboundActive.name: ciscoUnityPortsOutboundActive

ciscoUnityLicBridgeSessionsMax.name: ciscoUnityLicBridgeSessionsMax

ciscoUnityLicMaxMsgRecLenIsLic.name: ciscoUnityLicMaxMsgRecLenIsLic

ciscoUnityLicPoolingIsEnabled.name: ciscoUnityLicPoolingIsEnabled
ciscoUnityLicPoolingIsEnabled.description: This indicates whether or not license pooling is enabled for this server.

ciscoUnityLicVPIMIsLicensed.name: ciscoUnityLicVPIMIsLicensed

ciscoUnityLicPrimaryServerIsLic.name: ciscoUnityLicPrimaryServerIsLic

ciscoUnityLicSecondServerIsLic.name: ciscoUnityLicSecondServerIsLic

ciscoUnityLicUtilSubs.name: ciscoUnityLicUtilSubs

ciscoUnityLicUtilVMISubs.name: ciscoUnityLicUtilVMISubs

ciscoUnityEventType.name: ciscoUnityEventType
ciscoUnityEventType.description: The classification on the event severity. error(1) Error events indicate significant problems that the user should know about warning(2) Warning events indicate problems that are not immediately significant, but that may indicate conditions that could cause future problems. informational(3) Information events indicate infrequent but significant successful operations.

ciscoUnityEventSource.name: ciscoUnityEventSource
ciscoUnityEventSource.description: The software that logged the event, which can be either a program name, a component of the system, or a component of a large program.

ciscoUnityEventCategory.name: ciscoUnityEventCategory
ciscoUnityEventCategory.description: A classification of the event by the event source.

ciscoUnityEventId.name: ciscoUnityEventId
ciscoUnityEventId.description: A number identifying the particular event type. The EventID and EventSource can be used to troubleshoot system problems.

ciscoUnityEventDate.name: ciscoUnityEventDate
ciscoUnityEventDate.description: The date and time the event occurred.

ciscoUnityEventUser.name: ciscoUnityEventUser
ciscoUnityEventUser.description: The user name of the user on whose behalf the event occurred. This name is the client ID if the event was actually caused by a server process, or the primary ID if impersonation is not taking place.

ciscoUnityEventComputer.name: ciscoUnityEventComputer
ciscoUnityEventComputer.description: The name of the computer where the event occurred.

ciscoUnityEventDescription.name: ciscoUnityEventDescription
ciscoUnityEventDescription.description: The event description indicates what happened or the significance of the event.

ciscoUnityEventEMSNotes.name: ciscoUnityEventEMSNotes
ciscoUnityEventEMSNotes.description: The contents of the notes field as entered into the EMS for this monitored event.

ciscoUnityMonitoredEvent.name: ciscoUnityMonitoredEvent
ciscoUnityMonitoredEvent.description: This Notification contains information from the Windows Event Log concerning an event that the Event Monitoring Service is configured to monitor.
